<h1>@HI{{de}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}} @HI{{de}} ... 
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<a name="location"><strong>@HI{{de}}</strong></a> indicates the location of an action. Note that it normally cannot
indicate location of existence except in the case where it is used with @HI{{aru}} to locate an event.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinou @KJ{{silver^squat}}no@KT{{resutorann}}<strong>de</strong> @KJ{{nightfall}}gohanwo @KJ{{eat}}bemashita}}.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday I had dinner at a restaurant in Ginza.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<a name="means"><strong>@HI{{de}}</strong></a> indicates a means or an implement.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha @KJ{{day^book}}he @KJ{{boat}}<strong>de</strong>@KJ{{come}}mashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I came to Japan by boat.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{de}}</strong> indicates the materials used.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KT{{ke-ki}}ha, @KJ{{egg}}to@KJ{{sugar}}<strong>de</strong> @KJ{{make}}rimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This cake is made of butter and eggs.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{de}}</strong> indicates the greatest, least etc. in a comparison.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{generation^world}}<strong>de</strong>@KJ{{one^turn^tall}}i@KJ{{mountain}}ha @KJ{{what}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What is the tallest mountain in the world?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{de}}</strong> indicates the amount and scope.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{book}}ha 1@KJ{{time^interval}}<strong>de</strong> @KJ{{read}}memasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You can read this book in an hour.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{de}}</strong> indicates the mode or condition of the agent of an action.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{mountain^rice*field}}sanha @KT{{apa-to}}ni 1@KJ{{person}}<strong>de</strong>@KJ{{dwell}}ndeimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yamada lives in an apartment by himself.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<a name="time"><strong>@HI{{de}}</strong></a> indicates time or age.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{poem^person}}ha 25@KJ{{year-end}}<strong>de</strong>@KJ{{death}}nda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That poet died at 25.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<a name="cause"><strong>@HI{{de}}</strong></a> indicates the reason for something.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{ill^spirit}}<strong>de</strong>@KJ{{trip^going}}ni@KJ{{going}}kenakatta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Because I was ill, I couldn't go on the trip.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
Note that if you walk somewhere, the expression @HI{{aruite}} is used and the particle @HI{{de}} is not used in this case.
</p>

